'''GJ 1132b'''是一个围绕着[[红矮星|红矮星]][[格利泽1132|格利泽1132]]（Gliese 1132）（其体积是[[太阳|太阳]]的1/5）运行的[[太阳系外行星|太阳系外行星]]，距离地球39[[光年|光年]]（12 [[秒差距|秒差距]]），<ref name='Zachory 2015'>{{Cite journal|title = A rocky planet transiting a nearby low-mass star|url = http://www.nature.com/doifinder/10.1038/nature15762|journal = Nature|pages = 204–207|volume = 527|issue = 7577|doi = 10.1038/nature15762|first = Zachory K.|last = Berta-Thompson|first2 = Jonathan|last2 = Irwin|first3 = David|last3 = Charbonneau|first4 = Elisabeth R.|last4 = Newton|first5 = Jason A.|last5 = Dittmann|first6 = Nicola|last6 = Astudillo-Defru|first7 = Xavier|last7 = Bonfils|first8 = Michaël|last8 = Gillon|first9 = Emmanuël|last9 = Jehin|access-date = 2015-11-12|archive-date = 2019-10-16|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20191016211024/https://www.nature.com/articles/nature15762|dead-url = no}}</ref> 科学家认为该行星不适宜生命存活，但足够凉爽。<ref name="MIT News">{{cite news |last=Chu |first=Jennifer |url=http://news.mit.edu/2015/new-earth-sized-exoplanet-1111 |title=New exoplanet in our neighborhood |work=MIT News |date=November 11, 2015 |accessdate=2015-11-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151113214302/http://news.mit.edu/2015/new-earth-sized-exoplanet-1111 |archive-date=2015-11-13 |dead-url=yes }}</ref> GJ 1132b是[[智利|智利]][[MEarth计划|MEarth计划]]的成果之一。<ref name="Eager">{{cite news|title = Astronomers Eager to Get a Whiff of Newfound Venus-like Planet|work = Harvard-Smithsonian Center for Astrophysics|date = November 11, 2015|accessdate = 2015-11-12|url = https://www.cfa.harvard.edu/news/2015-24|archive-date = 2017-12-02|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20171202180543/https://www.cfa.harvard.edu/news/2015-24|dead-url = no}}</ref>

GJ 1132b被称为太阳系外被发现的最重要行星之一，它离地球的距离比任意已知的岩石行星至少近3倍，用望远镜就可以判断出它的大气组成、风速以及日落的颜色。<ref>{{Cite web|title = Earth-like world could be 'most important planet found outside solar system'|url = http://www.theguardian.com/science/2015/nov/11/earth-like-world-gj1132b-could-be-most-important-planet-ever-found-outside-the-solar-system|website = The Guardian|accessdate = 2015-11-11|first = Ian|last = Sample|archive-date = 2015-11-11|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20151111234333/http://www.theguardian.com/science/2015/nov/11/earth-like-world-gj1132b-could-be-most-important-planet-ever-found-outside-the-solar-system|dead-url = no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = Exoplanet GJ 1132b: the 'most important' ever found (Wired UK)|url = http://www.wired.co.uk/news/archive/2015-11/12/gj-1132b-most-important-planet-solar-system|website = Wired UK|publisher = |accessdate = 2015-11-12|last = Burgess|first = Matt|archive-date = 2016-04-03|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160403081508/http://www.wired.co.uk/news/archive/2015-11/12/gj-1132b-most-important-planet-solar-system|dead-url = no}}</ref> 它的体积比地球大16%左右，<ref name='Zachory 2015'/> <ref name="MIT News"/>并且是一个[[类地行星|类地行星]]。<ref name=Kowacki />GJ 1132b绕着它的红矮星格利泽1132旋转一圈需要1.6天，距離母恆星约140万英里。<ref name='Eager'/> GJ 1132b受到的恒星辐射是地球的19倍，<ref name='Zachory 2015'/>它的大气层表面温度估计有533 K（260 °C），它本身的温度估计比金星热。<ref name=Kowacki>{{cite web| url=http://www.csmonitor.com/Science/2015/1111/Spotted-A-rocky-Earth-sized-planet-close-by| title=Spotted: A rocky Earth-sized planet close by| publisher=Christian Science Monitor| date=2015-11-11| author=Eva Botkin-Kowacki| accessdate=2015-11-12| archive-date=2019-10-16| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191016211021/https://www.csmonitor.com/Science/2015/1111/Spotted-A-rocky-Earth-sized-planet-relatively-close-by| dead-url=no}}</ref>不過，它的其中一面可能溫度較低，這是因為它距離母恆星相當近，可能被母恆星[[潮汐鎖定|潮汐鎖定]]。但在大多數推測情形下，它擁有濃厚大氣層，可將熱能傳遞到遠處。

2017年4月6日，它被發現擁有大氣層，很可能是被水蒸氣籠罩的水世界。在體積與地球相當的系外行星裡，它是首個被發現擁有大氣層的系外行星。<ref>{{Citation|url = https://phys.org/news/2017-04-atmosphere-super-earth.html|title = Atmosphere around super-Earth detected|date = April 6, 2017|accessdate = April 6, 2017|archive-date = 2017-04-07|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20170407161842/https://phys.org/news/2017-04-atmosphere-super-earth.html|dead-url = no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Southworth|first=John|last2=Mancini|first2=Luigi|last3=Madhusudhan|first3=Nikku|last4=Mollière|first4=Paul|last5=Ciceri|first5=Simona|last6=Henning|first6=Thomas|title=Detection of the Atmosphere of the 1.6 M ⊕ Exoplanet GJ 1132 b|url=http://stacks.iop.org/1538-3881/153/i=4/a=191?key=crossref.f1eba309ebf4172d51db3143399477d3|journal=The Astronomical Journal|volume=153|issue=4|doi=10.3847/1538-3881/aa6477}}</ref>

